,"England":"England","Melcombe Regis, Dorset, England":"Melcombe Regis, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Insula","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Galician: habitational name from any of the places called Insua, meaning ‘island, peninsula (of a river or of the sea), land by a river’, from Latin <i>insula</i> ‘island’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Insula was born in 1126, in Sparsholt, Berkshire, England, his father, John de Insula de Lisle, was 22 and his mother, Ragnhilde Sumarlidasson Rognvaldsdottir, was 21. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Galiena Blount. He died in 1186, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1126–1186":"1126–1186","1129–1240":"1129–1240","1130–1198":"1130–1198","1153–Female":"1153–Surnud","1130–1175":"1130–1175","1155–1213":"1155–1213","1160–1250":"1160–1250","1104–1160":"1104–1160","1105–1182":"1105–1182","about 1160":"umbes 1160","before 1126":"enne 1126","1198":"1198","25 Dec 1160":"25. detsember 1160","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1129":"1129","1105":"1105","1126":"1126","1104":"1104","1213":"1213","Abt 1155":"umbes 1155","1155":"1155","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Sparsholt, Berkshire, England":"Sparsholt, Berkshire, England","England":"England","Melcombe Regis, Dorset, England":"Melcombe Regis, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1126–1186":"1126–1186","1129–1240":"1129–1240","1130–1198":"1130–1198","1153–Female":"1153–Kuollut","1130–1175":"1130–1175","1155–1213":"1155–1213","1160–1250":"1160–1250","1104–1160":"1104–1160","1105–1182":"1105–1182","about 1160":"noin 1160","before 1126":"ennen vuotta 1126","1198":"1198","25 Dec 1160":"25. joulukuuta 1160","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1182":"1182","1160":"1160","1129":"1129","1105":"1105","1126":"1126","1104":"1104","1213":"1213","Abt 1155":"noin 1155","1155":"1155","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Sparsholt, Berkshire, England":"Sparsholt, Berkshire, England","England":"England","Melcombe Regis, Dorset, England":"Melcombe Regis, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1126–1186":"1126–1186","1129–1